physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Sister 1 presented with amenorrhea at 15 years of age. Pubertal stage was Tanner B4, PH3–4. No clitoromegaly or fusion of labia majora. Sister 2 was prepubertal and presented with minimal hormone levels: estradiol <50 pmol/liter, testosterone 1.1 nmol/liter, and dihydrotestosterone 0.31 nmol/liter. No virilization of external genitalia.

physical_examinations.vital_signs: Thyroid values were normal; Prolactin 3.2 μg/liter; SHBG 3.2 mg/liter; Dehydroepiandrosterone 3.7 μmol/liter; Androstenedione 2.9 nmol/liter; Testosterone 3.9 nmol/liter; Estradiol 121 pmol/liter; Dihydrotestosterone 0.17 nmol/liter.
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Chromosomal analysis revealed a 46,XY karyotype in both sisters. Sonographic examination showed no ovaries in both cases. Histological examination revealed normal fallopian tubes and streak gonads bilaterally, with Sister 1 having a gonadoblastoma.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Gonadectomy was performed for both sisters, after which chromosomal analysis confirmed a 46,XY karyotype with similar findings.
